t that all of the effort was in the planning, which I had already done.  <br><br>I know this probably sounds confusing.  It's late, and I'm frustrated and tired.  Why?  I spent 9 1/2 hours camping Lynuga and she never spawned.  The ranger stuck it out for about 4 hours, and the druid, God bless her, was there with me the entire time.  We killed every thing we saw.  Named, unnamed, you name it.  But no Lynuga.  We were right in front of guk, where I was told she would spawn.  Has this happened to anyone else?  I'm sooooo mad at myself for buying those rubies.  <br><br>I would just like to hear from someone, anyone, who has completed this quest.  Where did she spawn?  How long between pops?  What are her place holders?  What race/class did you use for the quest?  How many earrings/rubies did you have?  Thanks fellow wizzies, once again for listening.   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Altheah Firesword<br>48th season<br>Veeshan <br>     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uronos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ronos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/1/00 4:39:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ivandyr's Hoop -- HELP ME!!!</span><hr size=1> When I did it killing Forager grix or krix something like that seemed to help, need to kill the &quot;light&quot; race npc that spawn but leave the troll slayers alone. She spawned within an hour of clearing them. Being a DE helps because I care little for faction of good races. <br>6 hoops<br>4 midnight Mallets<br>23 of the other things<br><br>As a side note killing her give troll faction and the ruby for the skull quest. kill her enough to become non kos in grobb in theory. <br><br>Have a day<br><br>Ronos <p>"There are not fifty ways of fighting, there is only one: to be the conqueror."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthea1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thea1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/1/00 6:29:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hoop</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the info.  You're not going to believe what just happened.  I figured I pull my character up this morning before I start my day just to see if I can spot her.  Well she was standing right where I spent many hours camping her last night.  I went to cast on her to kite her to the island and &quot;Poof&quot; she was gone!  She despawned right before my eyes.<br><br>After she was gone I saw a bunch of good NPCs running around.  I didn't want to kill them because I'm a human.  Ah well... I will try again later on.  <br><br>I heard she's on an 8 hour spawn time table, but I'm not quite sure if that's accurate.  Grats on getting so many earrings!!! <br><br>Altheah Firesword<br>The Bloody Clans<br>Veeshan  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uailt.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailt</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/8/00 1:13:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hoop</span><hr size=1> I have spawned Lynuga 4 or 5 times using the following method:<br><br>- leave a friend (druid w/ tracking &amp; wolfform is good) outside of guk<br><br>- make a troll shadowknight mule<br><br>- take your mule into the shadowknight guild and ask the main Guildmaster (Hulkulk, i think?) &quot;who is Lynuga?&quot; He will respond by telling you how Lynuga left him and took up with some other troll, etc,etc..  it turns into a quest for the Helm of Hulkulk.<br><br>- this should spawn Lynuga somewhere outside of Guk, for your friend to track down and hail, while you log back on as your main.<br><br>This has worked for me multiple times, and I have used it to get the hoop for myself and several friends.  It's possible that was all just coincidence, but if you're tired of killing everything in the swamp, might give it a shot.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Ailt <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthea1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thea1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/8/00 11:18:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Got it -- finally!</span><hr size=1> Wow, thanks for the tip, but I don't think I'll be doing the quest again for a while.  After spending 8+ hours in Guk, killing evreything that moved, I told myself that I was nuts and I vowed to never camp her again.  Instead I planned to check Guk every now and then to see if she spawned.<br><br>The next morning I did, she was there, but despawned immediately.<br><br>About 4 hours later I logged on and checked again.  She was there.  A druid friend helped me with the quest (selling the 2 other items to the merchant on the island as she handed them to me) and after 27 rubies I got the earring.  Someone else started doing the quest after I had given her about 15 rubies.  He gave her a dozen or so and didn't get the earring.  I only had 32 rubies on me, and if he didn't show up to feed her rubies I wouldn't have gotten it either.<br><br>So the earring ended up costing me about 2kp.  It's an awesome earring, and I'm happy with the result.  I will take note of what you said, because I plan on starting a necro someday, and you never know ... I just may do it again.  <br><br>Altheah Firesword, 49 wizard<br>The Bloody Clans<br>Veeshan<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udolomite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dolomite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/14/00 7:14:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lynunga</span><hr size=1> <br>A question:<br><br>Is the quest doable while invis?  Otherwise i'm KOS by her.. maybe wolf form?<br><br>Dol.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uthea1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thea1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/16/00 12:14:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> hoop</span><hr size=1> I don't know about invisi, but it is possible to do in wolf form.  I was with a druid in wolf form who got the earring doing the quest.<br><br>Altheah Firesword<br>The Bloody Clans<br>Veeshan <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=86.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showNextMessage?topicID=86.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=86.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.emailToFriend?topicID=86.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.threadControl?topicID=86.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=86.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=86.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussio